<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 2:02AM CDT  by NWS Houston - Galveston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Wharton, west central Brazoria and north central Matagorda Counties
through 230 AM CDT...
At 201 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Van Vleck, or 9 miles northeast of Bay City, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
West Columbia, Sweeny and Wild Peach Village.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
